OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FPew study: Little change in
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FIndia's religious make-up  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fin 70 years                
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, All religious groups in India have     
OL,6, shown major declines in fertility      
OL,7, rates, a study from Pew Research Center
OL,8, has found.                             
OL,10,FAs a result there have been only       
OL,11,F"modest changes" in the religious      
OL,12,Fmake-up of the people since 1951.      
OL,14,FThe two largest groups, Hindus and     
OL,15,FMuslims, make up 94% of India's 1.2    
OL,16,Fbillion people.                        
OL,18,FChristians, Sikhs, Buddhists and Jains 
OL,19,Ftogether make up the remaining 6% of   
OL,20,Fthe population.                        
